      "acceptanceCriteria": "The primary QoI (normalized index of hemolysis, NIH) must be directly traceable to the clinical hemolysis threshold specified in the device submission.",
      "rationale": "The NIH QoI is defined and linked to the clinical threshold, but intermediate scalar fields used in the power-law damage model are not individually validated, weakening traceability. Achieved level 2 versus required level 3."
